{"id": "food_FOOD00059", "name": "Arabica coffee (food medium)", "category": "food", "organism_scope": "food microbiome / general", "aerobic": true, "description": "Food-derived medium: metabolizable components of Arabica coffee (Coffea arabica) [Coffee and coffee products] from FooDB, plus a standard M9 mineral base. Organic components use presence-based uptake bounds; FooDB content retained. Measured compounds with no BiGG exchange are listed under uncovered.", "namespace": "bigg", "provenance": {"source_type": "database", "citation": "FooDB v2020-04-07 (Wishart DS et al., foodb.ca). Content sources: DTU, DUKE, PHENOL EXPLORER, USDA.", "doi": "", "url": "https://foodb.ca/downloads", "notes": "Organic components mapped from FooDB compounds to BiGG via InChIKey/name. Mineral base added. Bounds presence-based; foodb_content retained. Unmapped measured compounds kept in uncovered (v2 completeness fix). IMPORTANT: composition values are taken from the archived FooDB 2020-04-07 CSV data release; FooDB's live food page no longer displays this bulk composition, so it will appear empty. Verify individual compounds via the per-component cross-reference links. Underlying content was aggregated by FooDB from USDA / DTU / Phenol Explorer.", "data_release": "FooDB 2020-04-07 CSV release (foodb.ca/downloads)", "food_record": "https://foodb.ca/foods/FOOD00059", "verification": "expert-curated (multi-source food composition; growth-relevant profile completed, FooDB noise removed)", "curation_date": "2026-07-17", "curation_sources": ["Ky et al. 2001, Food Chemistry 75:223 doi:10.1016/S0308-8146(01)00204-7 (caffeine, trigonelline, chlorogenic acids, sucrose in Arabica)", "Acids in coffee: review and meta-analysis, Crit Rev Food Sci Nutr 2022 doi:10.1080/10408398.2021.1957767 (organic acids green/roasted)", "Metabolite Profiles of Green Beans of Indonesian Arabica Varieties, PMC8632381 (sugars, acids, alkaloids, amino acids in mM)", "Green-coffee proximate composition, Int J Agronomy 2022 art.1317341 (protein, lipid, carbohydrate, ash)", "Green Arabica coffee oil fatty-acid composition, PMC8121985; Agronomy 2023 doi:10.3390/agronomy13102560", "Green-coffee mineral ICP-OES, Eur Food Res Technol 2025 doi:10.1007/s00217-025-04664-7; PMC6778417 (K, Mg, Ca, Fe, Zn, Cu, Na)", "Free amino acids in green coffee, Eur Food Res Technol doi:10.1007/BF01231078", "USDA FoodData Central / roasted-coffee panel (niacin ~16.8 mg/100g roasted, tocopherols)"], "curation_notes": "Curated as green Arabica coffee beans (dry weight); roast-dependent changes flagged per compound (sucrose and chlorogenic acids fall, quinic/acetic/niacin rise). Dominant utilisable carbon/energy substrates for a growth medium are sucrose (~8 g/100g) plus the organic-acid pool (citric > quinic > malic > acetic, ~2.6 g/100g total) and the chlorogenic/quinic acid pool; caffeine (~1.2 g/100g) and trigonelline (~1 g/100g) are largely inhibitory/xenobiotic N compounds rather than favourable substrate", "curation_added": ["sucrose with amount (dominant soluble carbon of green beans)", "free glucose and fructose amounts", "citric acid, malic acid, quinic acid, acetic acid, lactic acid, formic acid (organic-acid pool - the main FooDB omission)", "total chlorogenic acids quantified", "caffeine and trigonelline quantified", "total protein and major free amino acids (alanine, asparagine, GABA)", "total lipid + full fatty-acid breakdown (linoleic, palmitic, oleic, stearic, arachidic)", "quantitative minerals (K, Mg, P, Ca, Fe, Mn, Zn, Cu, Na)", "niacin with green-vs-roasted note; tocopherols quantified"], "curation_removed": [{"name": "Cholesterol", "reason": "Animal sterol, biologically implausible in a plant seed; FooDB predicted, not a coffee growth nutrient. Coffee's sterol fraction is phytosterols/diterpenes (cafestol, kahweol)."}, {"name": "17alpha-ethynylestradiol", "reason": "Synthetic pharmaceutical estrogen; absurd as a natural coffee constituent - FooDB predicted/contaminant artifact."}, {"name": "Cyanocobalamin", "reason": "Vitamin B12 is not synthesized by plants/coffee; predicted, not measured. Remove."}, {"name": "Retinol", "reason": "Preformed vitamin A occurs only in animal foods; implausible in green coffee. FooDB predicted."}, {"name": "Beta-Carotene", "reason": "Green coffee beans are not a carotenoid source; entry is predicted/negligible, not a growth nutrient."}, {"name": "L-Ascorbate", "reason": "Vitamin C is minimal in green coffee and destroyed on roasting; predicted rather than a real growth substrate."}, {"name": "Phytomenadione", "reason": "Vitamin K1 negligible in coffee beans; FooDB predicted, not a growth-relevant nutrient."}, {"name": "Co2+", "reason": "Non-nutritive trace cobalt; FooDB elemental dump, not a defined coffee nutrient."}, {"name": "Nickel", "reason": "Trace/contaminant element, not a growth nutrient of coffee."}, {"name": "Chromium", "reason": "Non-nutritive trace element; FooDB dump."}, {"name": "Selenium", "reason": "Trace, highly soil-variable, not a defining coffee nutrient; drop as noise."}, {"name": "Molybdate", "reason": "Trace micronutrient from FooDB elemental dump; not quantitatively relevant for coffee medium."}, {"name": "Iodine c", "reason": "Not a coffee nutrient; trace/contaminant FooDB entry."}, {"name": "Fluoride", "reason": "Trace, not a growth nutrient; remove."}, {"name": "Fe2+ mitochondria", "reason": "Compartment/redox-state artifact duplicating 'Iron'; consolidated into a single iron entry."}, {"name": "Iron (Fe3+)", "reason": "Oxidation-state duplicate of 'Iron'; consolidated into a single iron entry."}, {"name": "Starch C12H20O10", "reason": "Green coffee stores little starch; its reserve carbohydrates are cell-wall polysaccharides (galactomannan, arabinogalactan). Retain only trace; starch entry is misleading as a major substrate."}, {"name": "Dextrin C12H20O10", "reason": "Not a genuine green-coffee constituent; dextrins are process/roast artifacts. Predicted noise."}], "curation_confidence": "high"}, "components": [{"name": "sucrose", "bigg_metabolite": "sucr", "exchange": "EX_sucr_e", "lower_bound": -10.0, "upper_bound": 1000.0, "concentration_mM": null, "xref": {"reactome": "R-ALL-188980", "kegg": "C00089", "chebi": "CHEBI:15128", "inchikey": "CZMRCDWAGMRECN-UGDNZRGBSA-N", "kegg_drug": "D00025", "kegg_glycan": "G00370", "hmdb": "HMDB00258", "biocyc": "META:SUCROSE", "mnx": "MNXM1104180", "seed": "cpd00076", "metacyc": "SUCROSE", "sabiork": "1294", "inchi": "InChI=1S/C12H22O11/c13-1-4-6(16)8(18)9(19)11(21-4)23-12(3-15)10(20)7(17)5(2-14)22-12/h4-11,13-20H,1-3H2/t4-,5-,6-,7-,8+,9-,10+,11-,12+/m1/s1", "formula": "C12H22O11"}, "in_biggr": true, "exchange_source": "biggr", "mapping_method": "name_deformula_remap", "mapping_confidence": "inferred", "role": "sugar", "evidence_source": "Ky et al. 2001 Food Chem doi:10.1016/S0308-8146(01)00204-7; PMC8632381 (Indonesian Arabica, 31-56 mM in-bean)", "amount": "8.0 g/100g"}, {"name": "D-glucose", "bigg_metabolite": "glc__D", "exchange": "EX_glc__D_e", "lower_bound": -10.0, "upper_bound": 1000.0, "concentration_mM": null, "xref": {"kegg": "C00031", "chebi": "CHEBI:12965", "kegg_drug": "D00009", "hmdb": "HMDB00122", "biocyc": "META:Glucopyranose", "mnx": "MNXM1364061", "inchikey": "WQZGKKKJIJFFOK-GASJEMHNSA-N", "seed": "cpd00027", "metacyc": "Glucopyranose", "sabiork": "1407", "inchi": "InChI=1S/C6H12O6/c7-1-2-3(8)4(9)5(10)6(11)12-2/h2-11H,1H2/t2-,3-,4+,5-,6?/m1/s1", "formula": "C6H12O6"}, "in_biggr": true, "exchange_source": "biggr", "mapping_method": "name_remap", "mapping_confidence": "inferred", "role": "sugar", "evidence_source": "Ky et al. 2001 Food Chem doi:10.1016/S0308-8146(01)00204-7 (reducing sugars)", "amount": "0.2 g/100g"}, {"name": "D-fructose", "bigg_metabolite": "fru", "exchange": "EX_fru_e", "lower_bound": -10.0, "upper_bound": 1000.0, "concentration_mM": null, "xref": {"reactome": "R-ALL-189049", "kegg": "C00095", "chebi": "CHEBI:12923", "kegg_drug": "D00114", "hmdb": "HMDB62538", "biocyc": "ME